78 Amendment note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s859"},"text":"section 859 of this title","children":[],"tail":") repealed "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455/s1605/b/1"},"text":"§ 1605(b)(1) of Pub. L. 94–455","children":[],"tail":", cited as a credit to this section, which had duplicated the amendment to subsec. (a)(6) made by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455/s1307/d/2/A"},"text":"§ 1307(d)(2)(A) of Pub. L. 94–455","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id42982002-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2022—Subsec. (a)(6). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/169/s11003/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–169, § 11003(b)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “50A,” after “46,”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/169/s10201/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–169, § 10201(b)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “37,” before “41”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2014—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/295"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–295","children":[],"tail":" struck out “Paragraph (1) shall not apply to the tax imposed by section 59A.” at end of concluding provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2007—Subsec. (a)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/172"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–172","children":[],"tail":" substituted “if the taxpayer chooses to take to any extent the benefits of section 901.” for “if—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(A) the taxpayer chooses to take to any extent the benefits of section 901, or","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(B) such taxes are paid or accrued with respect to foreign trade income (within the meaning of section 923(b)) of a FSC,.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2004—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/357/s101/b/5/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–357, § 101(b)(5)(B)","children":[],"tail":", struck out at end of concluding provisions “A rule similar to the rule of section 943(d) shall apply for purposes of paragraph (4)(C).”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/357/s101/b/5/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–357, § 101(b)(5)(A)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “or” at end of subpar. (A), substituted period for “or” at end of subpar. (B), and struck out subpar. (C) which read as follows: “such taxes are paid or accrued with respect to qualifying foreign trade income (as defined in section 941).”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(6). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/357/s802/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–357, § 802(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “45,” before “46,”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2000—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/519/s4/2/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–519, § 4(2)(B)","children":[],"tail":", inserted at end “A rule similar to the rule of section 943(d) shall apply for purposes of paragraph (4)(C).”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(4)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/519/s4/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–519, § 4(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", added subpar. (C)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1987—Subsec. (a)(6). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/203"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–203","children":[],"tail":" substituted “46, and 54” for “and 46”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/499"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–499","children":[],"tail":" inserted at end “Paragraph (1) shall not apply to the tax imposed by section 59A.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—Subsec. (a)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/369/s801/d/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–369, § 801(d)(5)","children":[],"tail":", inserted provision disallowing a deduction for income, war profits, and excess profits taxes if such taxes are paid or accrued with respect to foreign trade income, within the meaning of section 923(b), of a FSC."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(6). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/369/s67/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–369, § 67(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", inserted reference to chapter 46."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1983—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/21"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–21","children":[],"tail":" inserted at end “Paragraph (1) shall not apply to any taxes to the extent such taxes are allowable as a deduction under section 164(f).”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/67"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–67","children":[],"tail":" repealed amendments made by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/248"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–248","children":[],"tail":". See 1982 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1982—Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/248"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–248","children":[],"tail":" provided that, applicable to payments of interest, dividends, and patronage dividends paid or credited after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-06-30"},"text":"June 30, 1983","children":[],"tail":", par. (1) is amended by striking out “and” at end of subpar. (B), by substituting “; and” for the period at end of subpar. (C), and by inserting subpar. (D) relating to the tax withheld at source on interest, dividends, and patronage dividends under section 3451. Section 102(a), (b) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us